<Layout 
  title="Bereavement Benefits | Compensation"
  description="Understand the bereavement benefits available through the UK Armed Forces Compensation Scheme. Learn about support for families of service personnel who have died as a result of service.">
  <div class="container my-5">
    <h1 class="display-4 mb-4">Bereavement Benefits under AFCS</h1>
    <div class="row g-4">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <p class="lead">The Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (AFCS) provides support for families of service personnel who have died as a result of service. This page outlines the bereavement benefits available and how to access them.</p>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Types of Bereavement Benefits</h2>
        <p>The AFCS offers several types of bereavement benefits:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Survivor's Guaranteed Income Payment (SGIP)</li>
          <li>Child's Payment</li>
          <li>Bereavement Grant</li>
          <li>Funeral Expenses</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Survivor's Guaranteed Income Payment (SGIP)</h2>
        <p>The SGIP is a regular, tax-free payment to eligible partners:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Payable to spouse, civil partner, or eligible partner</li>
          <li>Designed to provide long-term financial support</li>
          <li>Amount based on the deceased's salary and length of service</li>
          <li>Paid for life, regardless of any changes in the survivor's circumstances</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Child's Payment</h2>
        <p>Financial support for eligible children:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Payable to children under 18 (or under 23 if in full-time education)</li>
          <li>Amount depends on the child's age and circumstances</li>
          <li>Can be paid directly to the child or their guardian</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Bereavement Grant</h2>
        <p>A one-off, tax-free lump sum payment:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Intended to provide immediate financial support</li>
          <li>Typically paid to the spouse, civil partner, or eligible partner</li>
          <li>If no eligible partner, may be paid to children or parents</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Funeral Expenses</h2>
        <p>The AFCS can contribute to funeral costs:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Covers reasonable funeral expenses</li>
          <li>May include costs of transportation and a headstone</li>
          <li>Claims should be submitted with supporting receipts</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Eligibility and Application</h2>
        <p>To claim bereavement benefits:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The death must be attributable to service</li>
          <li>Claims should be made as soon as possible after the death</li>
          <li>Supporting documentation, such as death certificate and proof of relationship, will be required</li>
          <li>Assistance is available to help with the application process</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Related Information</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
              <li><a href="/compensation/lump-sum-payments" class="text-decoration-none">Lump Sum Payments</a></li>
              <li><a href="/support/bereavement-counselling" class="text-decoration-none">Bereavement Counselling</a></li>
              <li><a href="/financial/pension-planning" class="text-decoration-none">Pension Planning</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Bereavement Support</h3>
            <p>For guidance on bereavement benefits and support, contact our dedicated team.</p>
            <a href="/bereavement-support" class="btn btn-primary">Get Support</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
